1
00:00:01,371 --> 00:00:03,954
(gentle music)

2
00:00:13,310 --> 00:00:15,050
- [Announcer] The following dramatization

3
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:16,800
is based on official documents,

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,523
personal interviews
and published accounts.

5
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:22,890
- [Radio Operator] Angel
Flight 8-6, Alpha Bravo,

6
00:00:22,890 --> 00:00:26,435
you are clear to taxi
via Alpha for runway 2-6.

7
00:00:26,435 --> 00:00:28,580
- [Rick] Tower, 8-6 Alpha Bravo,

8
00:00:28,580 --> 00:00:30,534
ready for takeoff on 2-6.

9
00:00:30,534 --> 00:00:32,531
Confirm my FR flight plan.

10
00:00:32,531 --> 00:00:33,364
- [Radio Operator] Alpha Bravo.

11
00:00:33,364 --> 00:00:37,090
Clear for takeoff on
2-6 (speaking faintly).

12
00:00:37,090 --> 00:00:41,120
- Alpha Bravo, climbing on
runway heading for 7,000.

13
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:41,953
Good day, Sir.

14
00:00:43,230 --> 00:00:44,730
I hope you're all tied down back there.

15
00:00:44,730 --> 00:00:46,320
We got takeoff clearance.

16
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:49,050
- Brad, you can get that later.

17
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:50,660
- I got that, no problem.

18
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:53,410
(dramatic music)

19
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:04,480
I'll get to that later.

20
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,453
- All set, Chuck.

21
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:12,560
How 'bout you, you need a hand up there?

22
00:01:14,746 --> 00:01:19,746
(engine revving)
(inspirational music)

23
00:01:40,786 --> 00:01:43,898
- So, what are you doin' this weekend?

24
00:01:43,898 --> 00:01:47,780
- (chuckles) My son, Travis
is learning how to cook.

25
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:49,780
I'll let him handle the kitchen,

26
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:51,533
I'll make a fire, curl up with Bob.

27
00:01:52,810 --> 00:01:56,338
- Well, wake me up when we get there.

28
00:01:56,338 --> 00:01:59,171
(music continues)

29
00:02:01,334 --> 00:02:04,167
(engine whirring)

30
00:02:10,837 --> 00:02:13,754
(wheels skidding)

31
00:02:19,406 --> 00:02:22,310
(siren wailing)

32
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:24,670
- Okay, hon, one more cough.

33
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:25,868
- [Woman] I know I
should've looked after here.

34
00:02:25,868 --> 00:02:26,935
(Sammy coughs)

35
00:02:26,935 --> 00:02:30,120
- And again.
(Sammy coughing)

36
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:33,030
Just to be on the safe side,
I'd like to do an x-ray.

37
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:34,554
- [Man] Why, what's the matter?

38
00:02:34,554 --> 00:02:35,387
- I'm not sure.
- Telephone call

39
00:02:35,387 --> 00:02:36,220
for Dr. Johnson.

40
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:37,053
- I need a closer look.
- Telephone call

41
00:02:37,053 --> 00:02:38,273
for Dr. Johnson.
- Let's go.

42
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:41,250
- Hey, come on, pumpkin.

43
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,130
Let's go see what you look
like on the inside, okay?

44
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:44,500
Come on (grunts).

45
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,590
Yeah.

46
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:48,640
- What's that?
- Pretty sure it's metal,

47
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,163
something she swallowed.

48
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:56,750
There's a non-surgical
procedure we can try

49
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:57,850
to get it outta there.

50
00:02:59,390 --> 00:03:00,223
OR, please.

51
00:03:01,486 --> 00:03:06,486
(monitor beeping)
(nurses speaking faintly)

52
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:08,771
- [Doctor] There we go.

53
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:13,082
Yeah.

54
00:03:13,082 --> 00:03:13,915
Wait.

55
00:03:15,025 --> 00:03:16,033
What's her blood pressure?

56
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:17,521
- [Nurse] 140/95.

57
00:03:17,521 --> 00:03:19,630
(beeping increases)

58
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:20,580
- [Doctor] How's her heart rate?

59
00:03:20,580 --> 00:03:21,426
- [Nurse] 99.

60
00:03:21,426 --> 00:03:24,241
(beeping increases)

61
00:03:24,241 --> 00:03:25,074
- [Doctor] What's her heart rate now?

62
00:03:25,074 --> 00:03:29,013
- [Nurse] 125, 129, 131, 139.

63
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,466
She's tachy-ing.

64
00:03:32,466 --> 00:03:33,299
140.

65
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,326
- [Doctor] She can't take it.

66
00:03:36,326 --> 00:03:39,000
(monitor beeping rapidly)

67
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,090
- We did a bronchoscopy, but
we were unable to remove it.

68
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:44,860
We can't operate here, it's too risky.

69
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:46,680
There's an infection that could spread

70
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,460
to the heart or the lungs.

71
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:49,690
We have to fly her immediately

72
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:51,730
to Children's Hospital in Denver.

73
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:54,983
I can't overstate this, her
condition is extremely serious.

74
00:03:56,170 --> 00:03:58,180
- My wife's terrified of flying.

75
00:03:58,180 --> 00:04:00,530
- [Doctor] A seven hour
drive is too dangerous.

76
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,330
- I'll fly with Sammy.

77
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:06,370
- I'll make the arrangements.

78
00:04:06,370 --> 00:04:09,190
- You go with Mom and I'll meet you

79
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:10,817
at the hospital in Denver.

80
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:15,817
(solemn music)
(Jack panting)

81
00:04:20,569 --> 00:04:21,470
(phone ringing)

82
00:04:21,470 --> 00:04:22,637
- I'll get it.

83
00:04:24,781 --> 00:04:26,281
Bagshaw residence.

84
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:30,263
Okay, I'll be in in 20 minutes.

85
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,570
- [Travis] Who was that?

86
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:34,860
- Sorry, honey, I gotta go back to work.

87
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:35,693
Why don't you come with me?

88
00:04:35,693 --> 00:04:37,200
You can ride back with dad.

89
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,160
- [Travis] But you just got home.

90
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,640
- I have to go, we're flying a little girl

91
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,120
to Denver for surgery.

92
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,820
- Mom, there's a big storm comin' in.

93
00:04:43,820 --> 00:04:45,933
- I know, we'll get out before it hits.

94
00:04:47,834 --> 00:04:50,113
Aw, Travis, what's the matter?

95
00:04:51,614 --> 00:04:56,300
- I just wish you weren't
flyin' Angel Flights anymore.

96
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:57,750
I mean, look at it out there.

97
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:00,573
- Hey, it's my job.

98
00:05:07,706 --> 00:05:10,956
I'll be back in time for your birthday.

99
00:05:12,128 --> 00:05:14,795
(siren wailing)

100
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,753
- Hey, good lookin'.

101
00:05:25,753 --> 00:05:27,190
- I gotta fly out to Denver,
a little girl is sick.

102
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:28,023
- Oh, terrific.

103
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,360
- Listen, take Travis home.

104
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,274
He's worried about me.

105
00:05:32,274 --> 00:05:34,914
- He's worried about you and
he's not worried about me?

106
00:05:34,914 --> 00:05:36,700
- (chuckles) He's worried about
you flying the chopper too,

107
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,533
but he won't admit it.

108
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:38,870
- Yeah, we'll talk about
this when you get back.

109
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:39,703
You gotta hurry.

110
00:05:39,703 --> 00:05:40,626
- Okay.
- Love you.

111
00:05:40,626 --> 00:05:42,125
- Love you.

112
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:43,802
(upbeat rock music playing)

113
00:05:43,802 --> 00:05:46,635
(window whirring)

114
00:05:48,078 --> 00:05:49,950
- You're a tough guy aren't you, buddy?

115
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,250
Ready to do it, killer?

116
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:52,107
Come on.

117
00:05:52,107 --> 00:05:53,383
- Daddy, come with me, I'm scared.

118
00:05:53,383 --> 00:05:54,770
- Just do it by yourself.

119
00:05:54,770 --> 00:05:55,603
There you go.
(horn honking)

120
00:05:55,603 --> 00:05:57,740
There you go, Justin,
that's it, bend your knees.

121
00:05:57,740 --> 00:05:59,066
Piece of cake. Yeah!

122
00:05:59,066 --> 00:06:00,282
Oh!

123
00:06:00,282 --> 00:06:01,115
You okay there?

124
00:06:01,115 --> 00:06:02,850
- Hey, you guys.

125
00:06:02,850 --> 00:06:04,550
What in the world's goin' on, huh?

126
00:06:05,482 --> 00:06:06,399
- You okay?

127
00:06:07,782 --> 00:06:08,846
- I'm okay, Daddy.

128
00:06:08,846 --> 00:06:11,880
- [Angie] You okay, sweetie?

129
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:12,862
- Gotta do it by himself.

130
00:06:12,862 --> 00:06:14,980
That's the only way
he's gonna learn, right?

131
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,330
- Honey, we need to talk.

132
00:06:16,330 --> 00:06:18,366
I think that we should just put Justin

133
00:06:18,366 --> 00:06:20,143
in the church kindergarten.

134
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,130
- There's two things wrong with that.

135
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:26,397
It's at the church,
and it's at the church.

136
00:06:26,397 --> 00:06:27,650
(phone ringing)

137
00:06:27,650 --> 00:06:28,483
- Yeah, well, I know.

138
00:06:28,483 --> 00:06:30,380
Well, all have Justin's friends go there.

139
00:06:30,380 --> 00:06:32,280
I think that it would be good for him.

140
00:06:33,910 --> 00:06:34,743
Brad?
- Angie,

141
00:06:34,743 --> 00:06:36,720
I gotta get the phone, I'm on the call.

142
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,770
- Can we please finish this conversation?

143
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,240
- Yeah, Brown here.

144
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,620
- Brad, Teresa.

145
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:44,490
You gotta come in.

146
00:06:44,490 --> 00:06:46,650
- [Brad] Well, do I have
time to take a shower?

147
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:47,483
I've been-

148
00:06:47,483 --> 00:06:48,860
- [Teresa] No, the patient's
a two-year-old girl

149
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:50,400
with a fever of 105.

150
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,930
We're flyin' her to Denver.

151
00:06:51,930 --> 00:06:53,289
- I'm on my way.

152
00:06:53,289 --> 00:06:54,510
(phone beeps)
(pensive music)

153
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,352
I gotta go.

154
00:06:55,352 --> 00:06:56,503
- (sighs) Great.

155
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,467
- Come here, buddy (grunts).

156
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:06,447
Your daddy's gotta go and take
a plane to Denver tonight.

157
00:07:06,447 --> 00:07:08,090
- Don't go, Daddy.

158
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:10,910
- See, there's a little
kid like you who's sick,

159
00:07:10,910 --> 00:07:12,110
and we gotta try to save her life.

160
00:07:12,110 --> 00:07:16,347
- This is the way that it
always is, you know that?

161
00:07:16,347 --> 00:07:17,700
- Angie, this is my job.

162
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,010
What do you expect?

163
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:23,433
- I expect you to give
Justin and I equal time.

164
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:26,693
Brad?

165
00:07:27,598 --> 00:07:28,681
- I gotta go.

166
00:07:31,662 --> 00:07:33,296
(Angie sighs)

167
00:07:33,296 --> 00:07:36,046
(pensive music)

168
00:07:38,683 --> 00:07:39,516
Hey, Maria.

169
00:07:39,516 --> 00:07:41,010
- [Maria] Hey, Brad, have a good one.

170
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:42,642
See you tomorrow.

171
00:07:42,642 --> 00:07:43,910
- [Teresa] We better move out.

172
00:07:43,910 --> 00:07:44,743
- [Brad] How's she doin'?

173
00:07:44,743 --> 00:07:46,280
- Not so good.

174
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,530
We didn't have time to
make introductions before.

175
00:07:48,530 --> 00:07:50,120
I'm Teresa Bagshaw.

176
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:50,953
I'll be the flight nurse.

177
00:07:50,953 --> 00:07:52,160
- I'm Jack Bahr.

178
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,450
- Brad Brown.

179
00:07:53,450 --> 00:07:56,071
- My wife Patty and my mother Loretta.

180
00:07:56,071 --> 00:07:57,830
- Just kiss me, Mommy.

181
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:59,247
- Oh, sweetheart!

182
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:02,993
- I want Bow.

183
00:08:04,676 --> 00:08:05,509
- [Teresa] What's that?

184
00:08:05,509 --> 00:08:06,963
- That's what she calls her bear.

185
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:10,347
- Hey there, Bow.

186
00:08:11,843 --> 00:08:14,385
Gonna take good care of you too.

187
00:08:14,385 --> 00:08:17,052
(phone ringing)

188
00:08:18,005 --> 00:08:19,543
- Hey?
(Patty whimpers)

189
00:08:19,543 --> 00:08:21,423
Hey, everything's gonna
be all right, okay?

190
00:08:22,421 --> 00:08:24,133
I love you.

191
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:25,420
- Okay, we're all set.

192
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,420
Let's get a move on.

193
00:08:27,401 --> 00:08:30,651
(man speaking faintly)

194
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:32,566
Heading for Denver.

195
00:08:32,566 --> 00:08:34,601
I want you to keep an
eye on the stretcher.

196
00:08:34,601 --> 00:08:35,518
Be careful.

197
00:08:38,577 --> 00:08:39,744
Watch that IV.

198
00:08:40,730 --> 00:08:41,730
- IV's fine.

199
00:08:42,928 --> 00:08:44,345
- And here we go.

200
00:08:48,156 --> 00:08:48,989
All right.

201
00:08:48,989 --> 00:08:51,656
(siren wailing)

202
00:09:05,351 --> 00:09:08,184
(EMTs chattering)

203
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,423
- I got the right.
- All right.

204
00:09:19,262 --> 00:09:20,615
- [Teresa] Look her over.

205
00:09:20,615 --> 00:09:24,615
- And one, two, three (grunts).

206
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,233
- [Teresa] Put her down.

207
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,371
How's the IV?

208
00:09:28,371 --> 00:09:29,974
Good.

209
00:09:29,974 --> 00:09:31,057
Put her down.

210
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:34,086
- Goin' down.
- Bring it down.

211
00:09:34,086 --> 00:09:35,507
- One, two, three, go.

212
00:09:35,507 --> 00:09:38,090
(somber music)

213
00:09:42,398 --> 00:09:45,231
(engine whirring)

214
00:09:46,811 --> 00:09:48,228
- Jack, let's go.

215
00:09:50,619 --> 00:09:53,334
- Yo, Brad, how you doin'?

216
00:09:53,334 --> 00:09:55,980
- How you doin', Rick?

217
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:56,900
Jack, this is Rick.

218
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:57,860
He's our pilot.

219
00:09:57,860 --> 00:10:00,060
Rick, this is Jack Bahr,
he's the patient's father.

220
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:00,893
- Welcome aboard.

221
00:10:00,893 --> 00:10:01,964
- Thanks.
- Jack, come over,

222
00:10:01,964 --> 00:10:03,550
sit over here.

223
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:04,383
Hey, buddy.

224
00:10:05,359 --> 00:10:07,203
- Hey, what'd you do, break your razor?

225
00:10:07,203 --> 00:10:09,106
(Rick chuckles)

226
00:10:09,106 --> 00:10:11,140
(engine whirring)

227
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:12,720
- [Teresa] I'm gonna do this real quick.

228
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,620
Gosh, you're good.

229
00:10:15,651 --> 00:10:16,883
Is that bothering you?

230
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:19,090
I'll make it more comfy.

231
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:20,490
That okay now?

232
00:10:20,490 --> 00:10:22,150
- Mrs. Bagshaw?

233
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:23,280
- Teresa.

234
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:25,950
- Shouldn't be in some sort
of infant seat or something?

235
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:27,250
- She's strapped in tight.

236
00:10:28,431 --> 00:10:30,670
- Alpha, IFR flight to Denver.

237
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:32,647
I have information landing.

238
00:10:32,647 --> 00:10:35,050
- [Tower Control] Air
ambulance 8-6, Delta Bravo.

239
00:10:35,050 --> 00:10:38,570
You are clear to taxi on
IFR flight, gray junction.

240
00:10:39,815 --> 00:10:43,898
- [Rick] Alpha Bravo, I'll
make sure, no problem.

241
00:10:44,950 --> 00:10:46,570
- This is an air ambulance.

242
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:48,850
It's equipped for any
kind of medical emergency.

243
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:51,140
Got antibiotics, oxygen,

244
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:53,219
medical instruments, supplies.

245
00:10:53,219 --> 00:10:54,510
(Jack exhales)

246
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:55,343
- [Jack] Thanks.

247
00:10:55,343 --> 00:10:56,840
- Relax, Jack.

248
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,347
We'll be in Denver before you know it.

249
00:10:58,347 --> 00:11:01,264
(engine whirring)

250
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:07,420
- What's that on the window?

251
00:11:08,490 --> 00:11:09,493
- I'd say it's ice.

252
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:13,557
- Can the plane take off with ice on it?

253
00:11:13,557 --> 00:11:15,750
- (chuckles) Look, you're
gonna have to chill out, okay?

254
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,030
It's no problem.

255
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:19,875
- [Rick] 8-6 Alpha Bravo,
ready for takeoff on 2-6.

256
00:11:19,875 --> 00:11:21,523
Provide flight bearing.

257
00:11:21,523 --> 00:11:22,395
- [Tower Control] Alpha Bravo,

258
00:11:22,395 --> 00:11:26,562
cleared for takeoff (indistinct).

259
00:11:28,829 --> 00:11:29,662
- Alpha Bravo,

260
00:11:29,662 --> 00:11:33,267
climbing on runway
heading 2-6 to flight 101.

261
00:11:33,267 --> 00:11:34,455
Here we go.

262
00:11:34,455 --> 00:11:35,801
- [Brad] Yes, Sir.

263
00:11:35,801 --> 00:11:40,801
(engine whirring)
(exciting music)

264
00:12:31,028 --> 00:12:33,861
(monitor beeping)

265
00:12:37,767 --> 00:12:42,767
(singer vocalizing)
(music continues)

